    <description><![CDATA[&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About OKEx:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OKEx is a world-leading digital asset trading platform, providing advanced financial services to traders globally by using blockchain technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OKEx provides hundreds of token &amp;amp; futures trading pairs to help traders to optimize their strategy. We are also one of the top digital asset trading platforms by trading volume, serving millions of users in over 100 countries. OKEx derivatives remains a top-notch venue globally and has a daily volume of approximately $10 billion and is widely recognized as the golden standard in the industry. We believe the blockchain technology will eliminate barriers to transactions, increase the efficiency of transactions across society, and eventually have a significant impact on the global economy. We strive to make innovative achievements that change the world and never stop to improve on our customer experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Localization team enables our products to be accessible in 20+ languages globally. We have an agile team, working closely with cross- functional stakeholders and vendors to enable international language launches and continuous localization of all user-facing surfaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Localization Project Manager, you will work with cross-functional teams through the product development cycle from concept to launch for all localization products. We look for localization project managers that care deeply about the products they work on and can build relationships and drive the right level of process to ensure the success of product development in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Formalize the internationalization or localization process in partnership with the HQ of Localization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with localization program managers to execute projects, identify risks, manage queries, and other means necessary to aim operational excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifies areas in the localization project workflow that could be improved and escalates as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and contribute to continuous quality improvement efforts such as localization quality assurance, and bug triage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and manage linguistic assets, including translation memories, terminology, and style guides.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evangelize globalization, internationalization and localization best practices to cross-functional stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s, or Master’s degree, Information Project Management, Language Studies, or International Studies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years localization project/program management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with localization tools such as TMS, CMS, etc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with external localization vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills with an ability to influence and communicate through data, and experience working effectively across time zones and cultures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bilingual in Chinese and English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Haves:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities in a time-sensitive and deadline-driven work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge in internationalization best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Action oriented, dedicated self-starter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for crypto and blockchain innovations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;<p><figure><iframe style="width: 500px; height: 281px;" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/x9kSkBMcOuo" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></figure></p>]]></description>
